      "content": "Welcome to the \"Advanced Transaction Management\" chapter of our DataStream database documentation. This chapter delves into the intricate mechanisms that ensure ACID compliance, the cornerstone of reliable database operations. We explore atomicity, consistency, isolation, and durability, each a fundamental principle governing the behavior of transactions in our relational database system. Atomicity ensures that transactions are indivisible, maintaining data integrity even in the event of system failures. Consistency guarantees that transactions transition the database from one valid state to another, preserving the defined rules. Isolation ensures that concurrent transactions do not interfere with each other, maintaining the illusion of sequential execution. Durability ensures that once a transaction is committed, its effects are permanent, surviving system crashes and power failures. In this chapter, we also discuss advanced topics such as concurrency control mechanisms, including deadlock detection, semaphore-based techniques, and buffer pool management. We delve into the intricacies of transaction logs, write-ahead logging, and checkpointing, which are essential for maintaining data integrity and supporting recovery processes. Additionally, we cover advanced indexing techniques, such as B-tree, hash, bitmap, and spatial indices, and their impact on query performance. We also explore the role of query optimization, including cost-based optimization and parse tree analysis",
